<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h1><a name="Tue_Morning_Exercise_Using_the_g"></a> Tue Morning Exercise - Using the glideinWMS </h1>
<p />
<!-- ASP 2012 Defaults <ul>
<li> Local UCL_HOST = osg-ss-glidein
</li> <li> Local UCL_USER = user
</li> <li> Local UCL_DOMAIN = chtc.wisc.edu
</li> <li> Local UCL_CWD= ~/osg_school/glidein1
</li> <li> Local UCL_JOB= 555.0
</li></ul> 
-->
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Introduction"></a> Introduction </span></h2>
In this session you will try to run some compute jobs with glideinWMS.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Prerequisite"></a> Prerequisite </span></h2>
<p />
Learn how to use our <a href="https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Education/AfricaGridSchoolTueGlideinSetup?INPUT_USER=user" target="_top">glideinWMS installation</a>.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Run_a_simple_job"></a> Run a simple job </span></h2>
<p />
Create a simple test script and submit it as you have done yesterday.
<p />
Feel free to create your own test scripts, just make sure they run for at least a minutes (but not more than 5).<br>
If you feel lazy:
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins1show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">click here to show an example script.</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins1hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide test script.</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins1toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
<pre style="margin-left:4em" class="screen">
#!/bin/bash

uname -a
id
date
echo '=============='
env
echo '=============='
let a=$RANDOM%60+45
sleep $a
</pre>
</div></div> <!--/twistyPlugin-->
<p />
<br>
Write a vanilla Condor submit file, like you did yesterday, and submit a cluster of 5 jobs.<br>
Again, if you feel lazy:
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins2show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">click here to show an example script.</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins2hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide test script.</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins2toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
<pre style="margin-left:4em" class="screen">
Universe   = vanilla
Executable = myscript.sh
Log        = mytest.log
Output     = mytest.out.$(Cluster).$(Process)
Error      = mytest.error.$(Cluster).$(Process)
should_transfer_files   = YES
when_to_transfer_output = ON_EXIT
Queue 5
</pre>
<p />
<pre class="screen">
condor_submit mytest.condor
</pre>
<p />
</div></div> <!--/twistyPlugin-->
<br>
Now monitor your jobs using the usual Condor commands:
<pre class="screen">
condor_q user
</pre>
<p />
Also check what resources are available:
<pre class="screen">
condor_status
</pre>
<p />
For a glidein-friendly view, try out:
<pre class="screen">
/opt/glideinWMS/tools/glidein_status.py
</pre>
<p />
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins3show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Advanced</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins3hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide Advanced.</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins3toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
A similar result can be obtained with:
<pre class="screen">
condor_status -format '%-49s ' Name -format '%-10s ' GLIDEIN_Site -format '%-10s ' State -format '%s\n' Activity -constraint 'IS_MONITOR_VM=!=True'
</pre>
</div></div> <!--/twistyPlugin-->
<p />
<br>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Inspect_the_results"></a> Inspect the results </span></h2>
<p />
Once the jobs are done, can you tell me where they ran?
<p />
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins4show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Show hint 1.</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins4hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide hint 1.</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins4toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
Look in your output file(s).<br>
If you used the example script, it contains the environment of the node your job executed.
<p />
<pre class="screen">
less mytest.out.555.0
</pre>
</div></div> <!--/twistyPlugin-->
<p />
<br>
<p />
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins5show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Show hint 2.</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins5hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide hint 2.</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationAfricaGridSchoolTueExGlideins5toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
Look in the classad of your terminated job.<br>
There are attributes which tell you where the job ran.
<p />
<pre class="screen">
condor_history -l 555.0 |grep MATCH_EXP_JOB
</pre>
<p />
Extra credit: Format nicely the relevant output using <pre class="screen">
condor_history -format ...
</pre>
</div></div> <!--/twistyPlugin-->
<br>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Run_a_BLAST_example"></a> Run a BLAST example </span></h2>
<p />
Try re-running one of your BLAST jobs, possibly on the yeast database,
as <a href="https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Education/AfricaGridSchool12CondorBLAST" target="_top">explained yesterday by Scot</a>.<br>
<strong>Reminder:</strong> Submit from osg-ss-glidein !
<p />
Check and discuss the results.
<p />
